<noinclude>{{month|June}}
Events that occurred on 5 June.
==On Earth==
</noinclude>
* '''[[1946]]''' - Actor [[John Bach]] is born.
* '''[[1953]]''' - [[J.R.R. Tolkien]] writes [[Letter 137b]].
* '''[[1953]]''' - [[J.R.R. Tolkien]] writes [[Letter 137c]].
* '''[[1955]]''' – Harvey Breit writes an article on [[J.R.R. Tolkien|Tolkien]] in the ''New York Times Book Review''. Breit tells of  "Dr. [[Tolkein]]", and contains many more errors. Tolkien later writes [[Letter 165|an angry letter about it]].
* '''[[1959]]''' - [[J.R.R. Tolkien]] delivers the [[Valedictory Address to the University of Oxford]].
* '''[[1973]]''' - [[J.R.R. Tolkien]] writes [[Letter 352]].
* '''[[1973]]''' - [[J.R.R. Tolkien]] writes [[Letter to James A.H. Murray|a letter to James A.H. Murray]].
* '''[[2003]]''' - [[Andy Serkis]] wins the [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MTV_Movie_Awards MTV Movie Award] for "Best Animated Character", for his role as [[Gollum]]. His [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wdebYE103sA immortal acceptance speech] would win the [[2004]] [[wikipedia:Hugo Award|Hugo Award]] for "Best Dramatic Presentation, Short Form".
* '''[[2004]]''' - [[The Lord of the Rings Symphony]] at [[wikipedia:Atlanta|Atlanta]] Symphony Hall, [[wikipedia:Georgia (U.S. state)|Georgia]].
* '''[[2008]]''' - [[Forodrim]]'s 36th birthday celebration.
